                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Aug. 28 (PTI): The Supreme Court has held that the appointments committee of the cabinet, which decides postings of senior civil servants, is bound to disclose its reasons for turning down promotions or selections, so that it is not accused of arbitrariness.           
	Although the grounds need not be communicated to the candidate, the information should be accessible for courts, it ruled.                  
	 Shimla: The Students Federation of India has scored a sweeping victory in Himachal Pradesh. In results declared on Friday, the SFI has emerged victorious in the Himachal Pradesh University in Shimla.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Centre on Saturday released a Rs 5 commemorative coin on Mother Teresa to mark her centenary. Finance minister Pranab Mukherjee released the coin and a souvenir. He presented the first coin and a copy of the souvenir to President Pratibha Patil.                  
	 Hyderabad (PTI): A woman allegedly electrocuted her 13-year-old son in Nalgonda because he had objected to her illicit relationship, police said on Saturday. A case of murder has been registered against K. Shivamani.                  
	 Salem (PTI): Three persons have been arrested for cremating a 16-year-old girl, who allegedly committed suicide, without informing authorities about her death, police said on Saturday. The girl had allegedly taken her life by consuming poison on August 27. She was immediately cremated.                  
	 Ghaziabad (PTI): Three armed robberies were reported in Ghaziabad on Friday. A gang left with Rs 2 lakh from a trader after he had withdrawn the money from a bank. Dacoits also robbed a petrol pump and a farmer.                                                                                                                                              
